text: :thinking_face:

Since you usually see "fractional" applied to C suite roles, I don't know if I think of it as a synonym for "part time" as much as for "retainer consulting."  And retainer consulting -- true consulting -- is by definition all strategy, no execution.  I'd also think of it as _irreducible_ -- you couldn't strip "CMO" or "CFO" down to a series of tasks to be executed.

text: So, from the C suite, I think my hesitation would be that "fractional content marketer" maps to "content planner" and then I think, "well, okay, but I still don't have my 'I need content' problem solved."
